0. Abstract

The Linguistic Actuation Doctrine explains how natural language, when structured with precision and coherence, becomes an executable control layer for LLM-based systems.

This doctrine defines the mechanism behind:
	‚Ä¢	daemon consistency
	‚Ä¢	continuity kernels
	‚Ä¢	governance gates
	‚Ä¢	narrative-state stability
	‚Ä¢	cross-model persistence
	‚Ä¢	procedural adherence

It formalizes the central insight:

Structured language can act as code,
because LLMs respond to patterned meaning the way machines respond to instructions.

